So far I’ve “lived hard” for 86 of the 94 days in 2023. 

I’m currently on day 50 of 75 and let me tell you that #75Hard has lived up to its name. It’s been HARD. What I’ve realized though is it’s all mental. If you say you can do something you absolutely can. 

There’s been days I’ve wanted to quit. There’s been nights I’ve had to do my outdoor walk at 11pm. 
When I’ve had to read in the car on the way to an event. 
When I’ve had to chug 2 water bottles with 10 minutes left to spare in the day to hit a gallon. 
Or chugged a shake because I needed to hit protein - shout-out to @rocksdiscount for keeping ya girl fueled during this. 

I’ve still been able to go out, be social and live life but I made choices aligned with my goal. 

When you want something more than you don’t you’ll do what others won’t. 

The crazy thing is there is no tangible prize at the end of this journey. Only the ability to say I’m in the 5% of people that finish what they started with #75Hard. Out of every 100 people ONLY 5 finish. & that’s something to be proud of. 

I’m not finished yet, but we only have 25 days left. And unless I’m struck by lightning ⚡️ there’s NOTHING stopping me.

Truth is I’m not happy ALL day everyday, but I live a peaceful and happy life. Life is like your heart beat. There’s going to be up and there’s going to be downs. What I’ve grown to learn is to embrace those down moments as opportunities to learn. Learn about myself and learn how I can pull myself out of funks. Because we ALL go through things. The difference is how we choose to handle situation. 

• KEEP YOUR ROUTINE 
  When your mood drops you can sometimes feel hopeless. Then hopelessness leads to negative thinking “what’s the point”. You will then withdraw from the things that made you feel good - exercise, eating habits may worsen, you recluse from friends + family, THEN you’re upset nothing changes and it pulls you lower then when you started. So in short, get up and keep your routine best you can!  Which leads me into my next point 

• DO THINGS THAT MAKE YOU FEEL LASTINGLY GOOD 
  Go for a walk, buy a pocket of happy 💐, write to express emotions, eat a meal that’s not going to have you crash later, dance, sit outside in the sun, even take a nap - whatever makes YOU feel good and isn’t going to bring you down later DO IT!  Don’t turn to “comfort foods” that are going to lead to regret later. Alcohol ❌ it’ll numb you for a second but guess what when it wears off reality is still there. 

• ATTITUDE OF GRATITUDE 
  No matter where you’re at in life or what you’re growing through there’s something to be grateful for. So think about the good in your life rather than the negative pieces you’re faced. Life is about perspective. If you have a roof over your head, clothes on your back, food in your fridge, a healthy body, family - that’s a start. 

• RECOGNIZE WHAT BROUGHT YOU DOWN 
  Not every dilemma in life is avoidable. There’s some pretty inevitable things that happen in our life that we have to face whether we like it or not. But a lot of the time our frustration is caused by .. US. For instance when you snooze your alarm and your day is behind, you’re in traffic, forgot your lunch, spilt coffee on yourself because you were rushing and forgot a lid… who’s fault is that? YOURS. We need to take some accountability in our life. 

YOU CHOOSE YOUR DAY 🤍

Getting back to doing the things that fill my soul ✨
1. Church 🤍 when my life is a mess theres always one common aspect of my life that’s changed. That be - I haven’t been in church the way I should. 
I felt grounded and at home today @myrocksanantonio 

2. Resetting and recharging on Sunday. For me this is cleaning and revamping my “pocket of happy” for the week. The way your home is kept is often how your mind is kept. For me I need cleanliness and organization to perform well in life. 

3. Being consistent with my activity and nutrition. As you saw earlier this week my training hasn’t been where I know it needs to be, but I have a new program and I’m ready for this next chapter. Back on a nutrient rich plan already has my body and mind feeling better! 

We can’t control everything, but we can control how we react.
